1
00:00:05,622 --> 00:00:07,590
So what shall I bring
back for the mother?

2
00:00:09,226 --> 00:00:10,989
What does a mother's heart yearn for?

3
00:00:13,230 --> 00:00:17,189
Mother's heart? It only yearns
for her son's happiness...

4
00:00:21,037 --> 00:00:25,531
no matter where he is... no matter
how he is... just happiness...

5
00:00:37,421 --> 00:00:43,951
And a son's happiness is in
his mother's laughter... her smile...

6
00:00:46,196 --> 00:00:48,494
something that he
isn't able to see.

7
00:00:53,270 --> 00:00:57,502
I promise, mother.
The laughter will return...

8
00:00:59,276 --> 00:01:04,873
that smile will return.
It's a son's promise.

9
00:01:10,987 --> 00:01:12,648
And a brother's!

10
00:01:34,377 --> 00:01:38,643
Your heart aches when your dear ones
go far distances, doesn't it?

11
00:01:48,124 --> 00:01:50,354
And when dear ones create distances
in between, it aches even more.

12
00:05:19,102 --> 00:05:22,367
Has your princess woken up?
- Oh yes... Pooja!

13
00:05:23,206 --> 00:05:26,175
No one knows her by that name. Call
her what she is called by everyone...

14
00:05:26,776 --> 00:05:27,902
Poo!

15
00:06:20,396 --> 00:06:24,355
You have no right to
look so beautiful.

16
00:06:33,009 --> 00:06:34,977
She has arrived, the cunning vixen,
to drop her daughter.

17
00:06:36,212 --> 00:06:38,680
After seeing your face in the morning
how can I call it a lovely day?

18
00:06:44,821 --> 00:06:47,187
Liar! Liar! Come here...

19
00:06:52,629 --> 00:06:55,189
Who is it, Anjali?
- Your future daughter-in-law.

20
00:06:55,932 --> 00:06:57,900
Come, let me serve you
some cornflakes.

21
00:07:18,254 --> 00:07:20,552
Anjali... Anjali I need to talk to you.
- What?

22
00:07:21,391 --> 00:07:23,655
This song that you sing every morning.
- So?

23
00:07:25,261 --> 00:07:26,819
It feels very nice.

24
00:07:29,199 --> 00:07:32,635
But the neighbours around
were complaining.

25
00:07:33,002 --> 00:07:36,165
I don't sing for them do I? I sing so
that my son learns about our country.

26
00:07:36,940 --> 00:07:39,636
Our Krish has learnt everything.
Say that you have!

27
00:07:40,009 --> 00:07:41,977
Yes... I have learnt everything.
- He has learnt nothing...

28
00:07:42,212 --> 00:07:44,510
he knows nothing about our country.
Our religion, our traditions...

29
00:07:44,881 --> 00:07:47,679
our heritage... Move out of my way.
Our country has...

30
00:07:48,084 --> 00:07:49,984
Oh stop it Mummy!
What country? Country!

31
00:07:50,220 --> 00:07:53,189
Eh! The country best in the world
is our India... don't ever forget!

32
00:07:56,926 --> 00:07:59,986
OK... I won't say anything.
He's already half an Englishman...

33
00:08:00,363 --> 00:08:02,593
when he turns a full one
don't complain to me.

34
00:08:05,001 --> 00:08:09,529
Yes... become just like her!
How do they say it? How do they talk?

35
00:08:24,754 --> 00:08:26,881
Wouldn't it have been better
to have lived in Chandni Chowk?

36
00:08:43,206 --> 00:08:45,470
Let me knot it for you, Jeej!
- Aaaah!

37
00:08:48,211 --> 00:08:51,669
What happened?
- What kind of clothes have you worn?

38
00:08:52,215 --> 00:08:54,183
It's become too long hasn't it?

39
00:08:57,220 --> 00:08:58,380
What now?

40
00:09:01,958 --> 00:09:03,516
Where's the back?

41
00:09:04,394 --> 00:09:06,328
Didi, don't wait for me.

42
00:09:15,038 --> 00:09:17,370
Anjali, Daijaan, come here.

43
00:09:17,740 --> 00:09:20,868
How do you allow Pooja to
go out wearing such little clothes?

44
00:09:40,964 --> 00:09:43,262
By the way even the two of you
are looking decent today, I think...

45
00:10:29,946 --> 00:10:32,141
You had worn this even the
day before, hadn't you?

46
00:10:34,183 --> 00:10:35,844
It suits you a lot!

47
00:10:56,973 --> 00:10:58,941
Poo... the whole college
runs after Robbie.

48
00:11:04,013 --> 00:11:05,708
He's not my type!

49
00:11:06,215 --> 00:11:09,184
Who is your type?
And when will you meet him?

50
00:11:11,320 --> 00:11:13,185
He might meet me anywhere... anytime.

51
00:11:16,926 --> 00:11:19,190
He could be right here somewhere.

52
00:11:21,964 --> 00:11:24,990
Oh God! Who is this... disturbing
Poo so early in the morning!

53
00:11:56,199 --> 00:12:00,260
Who is this who hasn't turned to
give me a second look? Who is he?

54
00:17:56,358 --> 00:17:58,349
Chandu's uncle fed Chandu's aunty
on a moonlit night in Chandni Chowk...

55
00:17:58,561 --> 00:18:00,358
in a silver spoon,
some Chatni...

56
00:18:02,965 --> 00:18:03,932
some chatni.

57
00:18:21,450 --> 00:18:25,546
Do you know Rohan, Didi always says
that a married woman is the union of...

58
00:18:25,921 --> 00:18:27,650
a wife and a daughter-in-law.

59
00:18:28,657 --> 00:18:32,889
She is a good wife, but she hasn't
managed to be an ideal daughter-in-law

60
00:18:34,897 --> 00:18:38,162
And your brother?
Not a day passes...

61
00:18:38,934 --> 00:18:41,164
not a moment passes when he
doesn't remember his parents.

62
00:18:42,371 --> 00:18:46,501
But he never says anything. He has
put up their photograph in the house.

63
00:18:47,943 --> 00:18:49,968
But not once has he
turned towards it.

64
00:18:52,214 --> 00:18:55,183
We have made a small world for
ourselves here, Rohan.

65
00:18:56,218 --> 00:18:59,187
If you look from afar
it's filled with happiness...

66
00:19:00,956 --> 00:19:04,483
but the closer you go,
you will find a lot of sorrow.

67
00:19:08,330 --> 00:19:12,198
Why have you come, Rohan?
Why now?

68
00:19:17,039 --> 00:19:23,672
I had promised bhaiyya that I will
never ask where he went or why he went

69
00:19:27,249 --> 00:19:31,276
But today I have realised that
he doesn't think of us as his own.

70
00:19:34,189 --> 00:19:37,818
That is a pain I can't bear...
can't bear.

71
00:19:39,328 --> 00:19:41,489
I have left some broken
bonds back home, Pooja

72
00:19:43,666 --> 00:19:46,157
that can only attain the status
of a family through my elder brother.

73
00:19:49,204 --> 00:19:54,972
I have come to take my brother back...
take my sister-in-law back...

74
00:19:58,213 --> 00:20:00,181
But I can't do this on my own.

75
00:20:03,018 --> 00:20:04,849
I will need your support Pooja.

76
00:20:08,223 --> 00:20:11,192
Will you support me?

77
00:20:18,167 --> 00:20:23,537
No... No... never!
- He is Sonia's brother.

78
00:20:23,973 --> 00:20:26,373
He's not my brother... And I didn't
even know that Sonia had a brother.

79
00:20:26,742 --> 00:20:28,642
So Sonia, when was this
brother of yours born?

80
00:20:28,877 --> 00:20:30,469
Brother? Who's brother?

81
00:20:33,182 --> 00:20:35,150
My first brother from India
has come.

82
00:20:35,884 --> 00:20:40,150
I mean first cousin.
He can't stay with me...

83
00:20:49,598 --> 00:20:53,159
It's only a matter of few days.
At least meet him once.

84
00:20:55,938 --> 00:20:57,906
My house isn't a charitable institution
that anyone can stay here.

85
00:20:58,207 --> 00:21:00,175
Daijaan, please explain to her...
- Why are you troubling him? Why?

86
00:21:00,342 --> 00:21:01,639
Oh stop it Aunty.

87
00:21:02,745 --> 00:21:04,838
C'mon, In such a big house can't he...
- Can't stay.

88
00:21:05,214 --> 00:21:07,978
This big house has you wearing
really small clothes... that's why.

89
00:21:08,350 --> 00:21:11,547
I don't want any young man staring at
you... And I'm the boss of this house.

90
00:21:11,920 --> 00:21:13,979
And I ring all the bells.
Gosh! What is it?

91
00:21:14,957 --> 00:21:16,925
What is it? I was just
saving you from an evil eye!

92
00:21:17,292 --> 00:21:20,853
Who's evil eye?
This whole family is mad.

93
00:21:21,230 --> 00:21:24,199
All the mad people from Chandni Chowk
have moved in here.

94
00:21:26,902 --> 00:21:31,362
Didi, Sonia's brother has just
arrived, he has no place to stay.

95
00:21:32,574 --> 00:21:35,805
Can't we give him a
small place in this big house?

96
00:21:36,879 --> 00:21:38,938
Pooja, You know Rahul, don't you?

97
00:21:41,917 --> 00:21:44,715
Didi, he has come from India.

98
00:21:47,189 --> 00:21:52,388
From India...
- My great India... remember?

99
00:21:54,196 --> 00:21:56,164
Listen to me...
- No... no...

100
00:21:57,199 --> 00:21:59,963
Just listen to me...
he has come from India.

101
00:22:00,335 --> 00:22:02,496
So? Should I make him sit on my head?
Do you know the population of India?

102
00:22:02,871 --> 00:22:04,839
If all of them shift here, where
will we sleep? Let me do one thing.

103
00:22:05,207 --> 00:22:08,973
I'll go to Heathrow and stand there to
invite everyone arriving from India...

104
00:22:09,344 --> 00:22:11,972
saying, 'Please come to my house.
My wife is mad!'

105
00:22:15,217 --> 00:22:17,378
He is coming today,
he's coming now, right now!

106
00:22:18,220 --> 00:22:20,313
He is waiting outside and
I'm calling him in...

107
00:22:25,227 --> 00:22:26,194
Listen...

108
00:22:29,164 --> 00:22:30,131
Excuse me...

109
00:22:39,241 --> 00:22:46,147
"We shall never part,
through smiles nor through tears..."

110
00:22:46,915 --> 00:22:50,874
"we shall never part,
through smiles nor through tears."

111
00:23:09,204 --> 00:23:14,506
"How helpless are we,
what is this trial by fire..."

112
00:23:15,210 --> 00:23:20,876
"we stand so close
yet we are so far"

113
00:23:21,550 --> 00:23:24,986
"If you are the body,
I am the soul."

114
00:23:27,823 --> 00:23:31,122
"I'm your blood..."

115
00:23:33,762 --> 00:23:36,196
"we meet and yet we don't..."

116
00:23:36,632 --> 00:23:39,396
"Oh what an illusion."

117
00:23:39,935 --> 00:23:45,134
"It's all your blessings,
whether smiles or tears..."

118
00:23:45,507 --> 00:23:51,878
"we shall never part,
through smiles or through tears."

119
00:24:10,199 --> 00:24:11,689
My name is Rahul.

120
00:24:17,940 --> 00:24:19,635
My name is Yash.

121
00:24:34,156 --> 00:24:38,183
He will stay with us.
Take his luggage...

122
00:25:20,702 --> 00:25:22,966
And this is your room!

123
00:25:29,211 --> 00:25:32,908
And listen...
if you ever need anything...

124
00:25:33,949 --> 00:25:37,112
want anything...
don't bother asking me for it!

125
00:25:40,856 --> 00:25:43,450
Listen...
- What is it?

126
00:25:56,171 --> 00:25:59,140
If you want to live in this house
you will have to follow the rules...

127
00:25:59,508 --> 00:26:02,807
and regulations of the house.
No coming late and try and...

128
00:26:03,178 --> 00:26:06,944
leave as soon as possible.
Dinner at 8 p.m. Or starve the night

129
00:26:07,316 --> 00:26:10,149
And... stay away...

130
00:26:14,189 --> 00:26:18,148
This is too much... Eh!
What are you staring at?

131
00:26:19,928 --> 00:26:23,625
Say more, Please... it feels nice.
- Eh! Feels nice? Am I singing a song?

132
00:26:23,999 --> 00:26:26,900
Why do you keep calling me
Eh'? I have a name...

133
00:26:28,637 --> 00:26:32,164
I know, but I can't say it.
- Why can't you say it?

134
00:26:32,874 --> 00:26:35,604
I said, that I can't say it. Didn't I?
- Oh!

135
00:26:36,011 --> 00:26:39,503
So you don't want to take my name
as a sign of respect. That's great.

136
00:26:39,982 --> 00:26:41,950
In that case I should return
the respect too.

137
00:26:42,217 --> 00:26:44,742
Can I call you Bhaiyya?
- Call your father that!

138
00:26:45,120 --> 00:26:49,784
Don't you drag my father into this...
actually you can... you have the right

139
00:26:53,362 --> 00:26:56,854
He got scared! Poo,
I think this one's a little...

140
00:27:02,237 --> 00:27:04,330
I'm mad? You wear this jacket.

141
00:27:13,248 --> 00:27:16,081
Rohan, we were waiting for
your call for such a long time.

142
00:27:22,391 --> 00:27:25,019
Seems like both of you
are right here with me.

143
00:27:29,331 --> 00:27:30,298
Mad!

144
00:27:30,766 --> 00:27:32,825
The campus is giving me
an accommodation after a week.

145
00:27:33,201 --> 00:27:35,294
Right now I'm living with
an Indian family.

146
00:27:35,937 --> 00:27:37,962
Why, an Indian family?

147
00:27:38,673 --> 00:27:41,836
They are very nice people.
When I met them I felt like...

148
00:27:42,210 --> 00:27:44,178
I have known them for years.
A laughing, happy and...

149
00:27:44,546 --> 00:27:48,175
contented family,
like we are... we were...

150
00:28:01,229 --> 00:28:06,690
Is he going to pay for the bill?
Go eat your food... even that's free...

151
00:28:23,251 --> 00:28:25,219
There goes Madonna
early in the morning.

152
00:28:32,360 --> 00:28:34,828
If you are here, who is singing
this prayer in the morning?

153
00:28:35,864 --> 00:28:38,162
Goddess Saraswati herself
has incarnated in the house?

154
00:28:44,206 --> 00:28:46,174
What has happened to
Saraswati here?

155
00:29:50,939 --> 00:29:53,169
Look what we have done, Pooja?
We have woken them up so early.

156
00:29:53,608 --> 00:29:54,973
Come on... take their blessings.

157
00:29:55,210 --> 00:30:00,170
Salutations Didi... Salutations Jeejaji
- Salutations to you too... Who is this?

158
00:30:01,483 --> 00:30:02,973
You are not able to recognise her
because...

159
00:30:03,218 --> 00:30:05,186
You are seeing her fully clothed for
the first time. It's your sister-in-law.

160
00:30:05,487 --> 00:30:06,784
You mean our Poo?

161
00:30:10,225 --> 00:30:12,716
Have a laddoo!
Mother has sent them.

162
00:30:13,962 --> 00:30:15,930
I thought I should
keep them as offerings.

163
00:30:16,231 --> 00:30:17,858
Let me do the tika for you.

164
00:30:22,237 --> 00:30:23,864
Won't you get your tika done?

165
00:30:25,574 --> 00:30:28,134
Back home no one leaves
the house without a tika.

166
00:30:29,177 --> 00:30:31,145
Mother says it's an auspicious
start for the day.

167
00:30:33,181 --> 00:30:38,141
Mother says?
So then... do it.

168
00:31:13,221 --> 00:31:14,984
Now who has done this?
- Me of course.

169
00:31:15,290 --> 00:31:17,190
I enjoy puncturing tyres.

170
00:31:18,560 --> 00:31:20,528
Was that a joke?
- It was... so?

171
00:31:27,235 --> 00:31:28,463
No I don't want...

172
00:31:28,737 --> 00:31:31,900
A guest is equal to a God. And you
can't refuse a lift offered by God.

173
00:31:32,173 --> 00:31:33,936
Come on go now.
- I'll take a taxi.

174
00:31:34,175 --> 00:31:35,904
Give me the money you would have
paid the cab.

175
00:31:38,179 --> 00:31:39,703
That I am.

176
00:31:40,181 --> 00:31:41,944
Listen... Please come back home
early in the evening.

177
00:31:42,284 --> 00:31:43,911
Why?
- Just!

178
00:31:45,654 --> 00:31:47,144
I have finished...
now let's leave.

179
00:32:07,208 --> 00:32:09,176
By the way are you
interested in cricket?

180
00:32:09,878 --> 00:32:10,845
Why?

181
00:32:11,046 --> 00:32:13,514
Because there's a match.
India v/s England... at the oval.

182
00:32:16,651 --> 00:32:18,619
It must be the last over.

183
00:32:19,120 --> 00:32:21,088
Is it a stolen car?
- No.

184
00:32:21,690 --> 00:32:23,180
Is it yours?
- Yes.

185
00:32:23,491 --> 00:32:25,186
Then do what pleases you.

186
00:32:44,879 --> 00:32:47,143
Don't say anything now. Anything
can happen at the last minute.

187
00:32:47,515 --> 00:32:48,948
You can never bank on India.

188
00:32:56,691 --> 00:33:01,890
Did you call me 'bhaiyya'?
- Why? Should I?

189
00:33:02,330 --> 00:33:05,163
Why? Just drive the car carefully.

190
00:33:09,537 --> 00:33:12,404
Hey! We won...
- We will win!

191
00:33:24,419 --> 00:33:26,387
Like every year
Poo will decide on the boy...

192
00:33:26,554 --> 00:33:29,455
who will escort her to the prom.

193
00:33:35,997 --> 00:33:39,626
You will be given marks on ten.
To go to the prom with me...

194
00:33:39,834 --> 00:33:42,803
you have to be brilliant in
three departments.

195
00:34:32,153 --> 00:34:33,916
You are not so bad.

196
00:34:34,389 --> 00:34:37,358
I wasn't talking about myself.
I was giving you points.

197
00:34:47,435 --> 00:34:49,403
I will go only with
him to the prom.

198
00:34:51,506 --> 00:34:53,133
Where will he go?

199
00:35:21,536 --> 00:35:22,730
Just fell.

200
00:35:32,814 --> 00:35:36,443
I'm leaving... I'm leaving.

201
00:35:39,420 --> 00:35:43,584
Listen...
I want to say something to you.

202
00:35:45,493 --> 00:35:47,461
Say it fast.
I don't have time.

203
00:35:48,162 --> 00:35:50,130
Should I say it?
- Say it.

204
00:35:53,935 --> 00:35:55,903
Should I?
- Please say.

205
00:35:56,671 --> 00:35:58,639
You have...
- Yes?

206
00:35:59,173 --> 00:36:01,641
You have...
- Say it please.

207
00:36:03,177 --> 00:36:05,145
Both...
- Both of us.

208
00:36:06,180 --> 00:36:07,943
Both...
- Both...

209
00:36:08,249 --> 00:36:11,150
Both... Both of your
shoes are not matched.

210
00:36:18,192 --> 00:36:20,888
That's the latest fashion.
I don't think you know.

211
00:36:42,550 --> 00:36:44,518
Please tell Didi
not to wait for me.

212
00:37:06,240 --> 00:37:07,366
Where are you?

213
00:37:25,293 --> 00:37:32,495
"From the moment
I set my eyes on you..."

214
00:37:34,769 --> 00:37:38,170
"I marked you to be mine"

215
00:37:44,245 --> 00:37:51,549
"Don't turn your back on me,
you are mine, only mine"

