of something and I don't turn it true.

469
01:16:55,494 --> 01:16:57,587
Tell me where you are right now,
we want to meet you just now...

470
01:16:59,231 --> 01:17:00,994
You are meeting me
after such a long time.

471
01:17:02,468 --> 01:17:05,801
Present? Now...
at this time... here...

472
01:17:06,138 --> 01:17:08,106
You meet me at 5 p.m. At
the Blue water Shopping mall.

473
01:17:08,640 --> 01:17:10,608
But tell me what
you want, my child.

474
01:17:10,976 --> 01:17:13,945
You will find what
I want right there, Dad.

475
01:17:31,864 --> 01:17:33,297
What's happening here?
- I'm looking for the receipts.

476
01:17:33,532 --> 01:17:35,500
What receipts?
- To return the clothes.

477
01:17:35,868 --> 01:17:37,836
If you have to return them, why do you
buy them in the first place?

478
01:17:38,270 --> 01:17:40,966
The country best in the world
is our India... Right Mom?

479
01:17:41,206 --> 01:17:42,173
Mother's stooge!

480
01:17:47,546 --> 01:17:49,673
Did you tape that? That Indian serial,
Kyon Ki Saas Bhi kabhi bahu thi.

481
01:17:50,115 --> 01:17:51,980
What a brilliant twist!
The son dies.

482
01:17:52,217 --> 01:17:55,186
Oh God! Really? Oh No...
You have given away the suspense.

483
01:17:58,223 --> 01:18:00,191
What are you doing?
- It's fine till the hugs

484
01:18:00,459 --> 01:18:02,927
- but he keeps kissing me too.
- You have never kissed me so much.

485
01:18:03,228 --> 01:18:05,196
Come home, darling... and see.

486
01:22:37,469 --> 01:22:41,132
Lies! You lied to me.

487
01:22:42,641 --> 01:22:45,132
Yes... I lied to you, Dad.

488
01:22:46,511 --> 01:22:48,479
What would I have achieved even if
I had told truth.

489
01:22:49,514 --> 01:22:51,141
I wouldn't be able to break
your ego.

490
01:22:52,718 --> 01:22:54,686
What else is it if not ego, Dad?

491
01:22:55,187 --> 01:22:58,247
That separates a mother from her child
that takes away...

492
01:22:58,523 --> 01:23:01,754
a brother from his sibling... that
throws a father away from his son...?

493
01:23:02,027 --> 01:23:05,485
He is not my son!
I don't believe that he is my son.

494
01:23:06,431 --> 01:23:08,399
Has he fulfilled the duties
of a son? He didn't.

495
01:23:09,534 --> 01:23:12,628
He did, Dad... he did.

496
01:23:16,007 --> 01:23:17,770
He always fulfilled them.

497
01:23:19,878 --> 01:23:24,178
He only made one mistake... Love.

498
01:23:26,218 --> 01:23:28,778
If that is a crime according to
your law, so be it.

499
01:23:30,555 --> 01:23:33,388
But isn't it your duty as an elder
to forgive him for his mistake?

500
01:23:36,962 --> 01:23:38,930
But you came down to punishing him.

501
01:23:43,168 --> 01:23:45,136
What kind of punishment is this, Dad?

502
01:23:49,174 --> 01:23:50,937
What punishment is this?

503
01:23:58,350 --> 01:23:59,942
Just look into my eyes and say that...

504
01:24:00,185 --> 01:24:02,153
you don't feel the pain
of parting with him.

505
01:24:04,089 --> 01:24:05,954
Say that you don't remember him.

506
01:24:07,459 --> 01:24:09,154
Say that you don't love him.

507
01:24:11,530 --> 01:24:14,260
Say it, Dad. Say it.

508
01:24:14,900 --> 01:24:19,496
I don't love him.
I don't love him.

509
01:24:20,739 --> 01:24:22,434
I said it, didn't I?

510
01:24:36,421 --> 01:24:41,120
God has blessed you
with everything, Dad... Everything.

511
01:24:44,763 --> 01:24:46,526
I just wish he had given you a heart!
- Shut up!

512
01:24:48,066 --> 01:24:49,397
You irreverent child!

513
01:24:57,175 --> 01:24:58,938
You love him.

514
01:25:02,614 --> 01:25:06,141
You love him a lot.
You love him a lot.

515
01:25:09,187 --> 01:25:15,148
I have got my answer.
You really love him.

516
01:25:18,763 --> 01:25:20,424
Let's go back, Rahul.

517
01:25:21,199 --> 01:25:25,499
It's too much now...
This is not our country.

518
01:25:26,137 --> 01:25:30,597
These are not our people.
We have set up a house here...

519
01:25:31,142 --> 01:25:34,111
but have you ever wondered
what kind of a home is this...

520
01:25:36,147 --> 01:25:39,116
that doesn't have a mother's
warmth or a father's blessings?

521
01:25:42,420 --> 01:25:46,117
Let's go back, Rahul.
Mother and Father are here...

522
01:25:47,158 --> 01:25:52,596
They are right here.
They are elders.

523
01:25:55,166 --> 01:25:59,728
They are a little angry with us.
But we will ask for forgiveness.

524
01:26:02,173 --> 01:26:06,132
Rahul... I know
they are as incomplete without us...

525
01:26:07,178 --> 01:26:09,146
as we are without them.

526
01:26:10,181 --> 01:26:13,150
We will ask for forgiveness, Rahul.
Let's go back.

527
01:26:18,590 --> 01:26:20,421
You will never understand.

528
01:26:24,930 --> 01:26:28,889
To turn a stranger into your own...

529
01:26:29,534 --> 01:26:31,502
and then to turn him back
to a stranger...

530
01:26:34,205 --> 01:26:36,173
you can never understand the pain.

531
01:26:38,376 --> 01:26:41,345
I agree they are elders...

532
01:26:44,215 --> 01:26:46,513
but even they don't have the right
to break a heart.

533
01:26:50,221 --> 01:26:52,519
Even they don't have
a right to break a heart.

534
01:27:15,380 --> 01:27:17,348
I think we should call him back.

535
01:28:00,325 --> 01:28:04,989
Yash, It was her last wish
to have Rahul...

536
01:28:06,231 --> 01:28:09,428
Just wait for a while... I
know he will definitely come.

537
01:28:11,403 --> 01:28:14,201
We don't need to wait
for anyone... Rohan.

538
01:29:17,602 --> 01:29:19,570
Rahul and Anjali are leaving.

539
01:29:23,241 --> 01:29:25,209
They are leaving tomorrow from here.

540
01:29:27,545 --> 01:29:29,513
They haven't even come home.

541
01:29:35,253 --> 01:29:36,550
If you say to them...

542
01:29:55,473 --> 01:30:00,501
Do you know mother always
says that...

543
01:30:02,213 --> 01:30:03,976
a husband is God.

544
01:30:05,617 --> 01:30:09,576
No matter what he says...
no matter what he thinks...

545
01:30:10,522 --> 01:30:12,183
he is always right.

546
01:30:13,892 --> 01:30:17,919
You brought Rahul home one day...
right.

547
01:30:20,231 --> 01:30:28,138
We gave him lots of love... right.
He became a part of our family.

548
01:30:31,442 --> 01:30:37,142
He became my life...
right... absolutely right!

549
01:30:41,052 --> 01:30:45,955
Then... one day he left home
and went away.

550
01:30:48,593 --> 01:30:49,560
Wrong

551
01:30:52,197 --> 01:30:56,156
You let him leave... wrong

552
01:30:59,204 --> 01:31:04,164
You separated a mother from
her child... wrong.

553
01:31:07,545 --> 01:31:13,506
Our family shattered
to pieces... wrong.

554
01:31:17,956 --> 01:31:20,186
Then how does a husband become God?

555
01:31:25,296 --> 01:31:27,457
God can't do any wrong can he?

556
01:31:33,504 --> 01:31:40,933
My husband is just a husband...
just a husband... Not God.

557
01:31:45,984 --> 01:31:47,417
Not God.

558
01:31:50,355 --> 01:31:51,652
Nandini!

559
01:31:53,191 --> 01:31:58,754
I said it... Didn't I?
That's it!

560
01:32:39,404 --> 01:32:41,372
Ever since the day you left,
Bhaiyya...

561
01:32:42,340 --> 01:32:44,137
mother has only seen you
through His eyes.

562
01:32:46,978 --> 01:32:48,138
He is the one who gave a mother...

563
01:32:48,313 --> 01:32:50,611
the strength to stay away
from her son.

564
01:32:53,184 --> 01:32:55,152
Please swear on Him, Bhaiyya...

565
01:32:57,188 --> 01:32:59,156
that you will come home
at least once.

566
01:33:01,125 --> 01:33:02,490
Just once, Bhaiyya.

567
01:33:04,195 --> 01:33:08,689
Even if it is for a moment.
Even if it is for a day.

568
01:33:11,369 --> 01:33:13,166
Let Bhabhi feel
at least once that

569
01:33:13,371 --> 01:33:15,339
she is the daughter-in-law
of this family.

570
01:33:17,208 --> 01:33:19,176
She is a part of the family.

571
01:33:20,211 --> 01:33:22,304
At least let your shadow fall
on the photograph...

572
01:33:22,547 --> 01:33:25,175
that has kept your memory alive in
mother's eyes for the last ten years.

573
01:33:31,155 --> 01:33:36,115
Just once, Bhaiyya.
Then you can leave

574
01:33:37,962 --> 01:33:42,126
No one will stop you.
No one will stop you.

575
01:33:47,271 --> 01:33:49,239
On the strength of that one memory...

576
01:33:49,574 --> 01:33:54,307
that one moment... Mother
can lead her entire life.

577
01:33:58,349 --> 01:34:00,544
Can't you do just this
much for mother?

578
01:38:20,578 --> 01:38:22,876
You took my words so much to heart
that you went away.

579
01:38:24,982 --> 01:38:29,749
Didn't even look back once.
Didn't come back even once.

580
01:38:31,622 --> 01:38:33,146
Didn't come back.

581
01:38:34,992 --> 01:38:36,960
Where did you call
me back, Papa?

582
01:38:40,598 --> 01:38:42,429
Did I have to call you back?

583
01:38:43,601 --> 01:38:45,330
Am I not elder?
Do I have to call you back?

584
01:38:45,569 --> 01:38:46,968
Am I not elder?

585
01:38:49,273 --> 01:38:51,173
I thought you didn't love me.

586
01:38:52,209 --> 01:38:54,074
I thought you didn't
think of me as your son.

587
01:38:54,378 --> 01:38:57,905
How could you think that?
How could you?

588
01:38:59,684 --> 01:39:04,178
I brought you into this house for
the first time with these hands.

589
01:39:06,223 --> 01:39:09,192
You completed our family.
You fulfilled all our dreams.

590
01:39:10,961 --> 01:39:12,121
How did you think...?

591
01:39:12,363 --> 01:39:16,197
I thought you didn't love me...
didn't love me.

592
01:39:18,235 --> 01:39:22,535
I love you very much,
my son... love you very much.

593
01:39:25,309 --> 01:39:31,145
Just... just couldn't say it.

594
01:39:33,384 --> 01:39:38,151
In these ten years I have thought
about you every moment every day.

595
01:39:39,457 --> 01:39:43,416
I thought of you so much that,
I felt like embracing you and...

596
01:39:43,661 --> 01:39:45,629
telling you how much I love you.

597
01:39:51,202 --> 01:39:52,965
Just couldn't say it.

598
01:39:57,208 --> 01:40:01,167
Elders' anger is a part of...
their love, my son.

599
01:40:03,114 --> 01:40:06,914
You took it so much to heart that
you got angry and left home...?

600
01:40:08,886 --> 01:40:10,854
And I didn't even call you back.

601
01:40:12,556 --> 01:40:15,923
Why would you call me?
I should have come on my own.

602
01:40:16,227 --> 01:40:18,593
Yes...
- I should have come on my own.

603
01:40:20,498 --> 01:40:23,934
Why didn't you come?
Why didn't you?

604
01:40:24,502 --> 01:40:27,528
This is your home...
You are the elder son of the family...

605
01:40:27,905 --> 01:40:29,873
You are my son... my son.

606
01:40:33,344 --> 01:40:40,477
And now I have grown old my son.

607
01:40:42,420 --> 01:40:44,149
I have grown old.

608
01:40:47,291 --> 01:40:48,918
At least forgive me now.

609
01:40:51,529 --> 01:40:56,660
At least forgive me
now... At least now.

610
01:41:35,172 --> 01:41:37,140
Come here, son.

611
01:41:46,517 --> 01:41:47,745
Son...

612
01:41:49,520 --> 01:41:54,150
At times the youngsters
in the house show the right...

613
01:41:54,525 --> 01:41:56,493
path to the elders in the family.

614
01:41:59,196 --> 01:42:03,155
I kept you away from your brother
for years.

615
01:42:08,539 --> 01:42:12,498
Please forgive me if you can.

616
01:42:13,944 --> 01:42:16,174
Forgive me... forgive me.
